  "text": "Peter provides a common understanding of sedation as \"slow euthanasia\" [CITATION_1] , but he clarifies for a patient how hastening her death through sedation needed to be slow if it was to afford him legal and professional protection. He identifies the ambiguous distinction between a legal action that may hasten death (inadvertently) and one that is more overt but illegal.",
